  "texts": [
    "The preceding section examines the implications of workers self-selecting into chatbot adoption based on their individual benefits.",
    "Beyond this margin of selection, at least two additional forms of selection may be at play.",
    "First, firms that choose to encourage chatbots may be the ones with the greatest benefits from the tools-even absent any encouragement initiatives-introducing potential reverse causality between employer encouragement and reported benefits.",
    "In the framework above, this corresponds to E being positively related to α b0.",
    "Second, employers may target their encouragement toward employees who are expected to benefit the most individually."
